President Trump made remarks during a reception at the White House, thanking members of Congress, his Cabinet, and the Supreme Court. He mentioned the accomplishments of his administration, including tax cuts, regulation cuts, and the appointment of two Supreme Court justices. He also mentioned upcoming legislation on criminal justice reform and the farm bill. The President praised the First Lady for her work on the Christmas decorations at the White House and expressed optimism about healthcare and infrastructure legislation. He wished everyone a Merry Christmas, Happy Hanukkah, and a Happy New Year.